# Receipt Upload v1 — Manual Testing Checklist

---

## 1. Access & Permissions

- [x] Regular member sees "➕ Quick Expense" in the sidebar after signing in
- [x] Unassigned / signed-out user does NOT see the sidebar button
- [x] Quick Expense page opens as a full-width overlay (Back to Dashboard returns correctly)
- [x] Quick Entry and Scan Receipt tabs are both visible on the overlay

---

## 2. Upload & OCR (Scan Receipt tab)

- [x] File picker accepts `.jpg`, `.jpeg`, `.png`, `.webp`, `.pdf`; rejects other types
- [x] Uploading a clear grocery receipt image → OCR extracts merchant, date, and line items with amounts pre-filled
- [x] Uploading a blurry/unreadable image → app shows "OCR could not extract line items. Add lines manually." and opens an empty review screen (does not crash)
- [x] Uploading when `[openai] api_key` is blank in secrets → same graceful fallback to manual entry (no error thrown)
- [x] Receipt date override field is respected (change date before uploading → review screen shows that date)

---

## 3. Draft List

- [x] After uploading, navigating away and back to Scan Receipt → the draft appears in the "Resume a draft receipt" list
- [x] Clicking Resume on a draft loads the review screen with previously saved lines
- [x] Clicking 🗑 archives the draft; it disappears from the list immediately

---

## 4. Review Screen — Header

- [x] Merchant, Date, and Total fields are editable and pre-filled from OCR
- [x] Changing merchant/date/total and clicking Save Draft → values persist when resuming the draft
- [x] If a storage image was uploaded, an expandable Receipt image section shows the preview

---

## 5. Review Screen — Line Editor

- [x] Each line shows Description, Amount, and Ledger Target
- [x] Regular member: Ledger target dropdown only shows Personal (and HH Obligation if they have obligation assignments)
- [x] Admin/developer: Ledger target shows all four options (Personal, HH Obligation, HH Shared, Project)
- [x] Switching ledger target updates the Category picker to match that target's options
- [x] Switching to Project hides the Category picker and shows the Project selector instead
- [x] ＋ Add line button appends a blank row
- [] Entering a non-numeric amount → field is ignored at post time (soft, not a hard block in v1)

